Effective Date: 20.09.24

OffsideWire ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our services.

1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information:

Personal Information: When you connect your TikTok or other social media accounts to OffsideWire, we may collect identifiers such as your username, email address, and profile information.
Content Data: Information regarding the content you create and post, such as captions, videos, and media files.
Usage Data: We collect information about how you interact with our app, including log data, device information, and analytics.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information in the following ways:

To automate and manage content posting to social media platforms, such as TikTok.
To communicate with you regarding your use of our service.
To improve and personalize your user experience.
To comply with legal obligations.
3. Sharing Your Information
We do not sell or rent your personal information. We may share your information in the following situations:

With third-party service providers, such as TikTok, to facilitate the services we provide.
If required by law or in response to valid legal requests.
To protect our rights, property, or safety, or the rights, property, or safety of others.
4. Data Storage and Security
We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your information. However, no online service is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your data.

5. Your Data Rights
You may request to access, correct, or delete your personal information by contacting us at offside.wire@gmail.com. You also have the right to withdraw consent for us to process your data at any time.

6. Third-Party Services
Our app may link to third-party services, such as TikTok. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these external services. Please review their respective privacy policies.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date. Your continued use of the service after any changes signifies your acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.

8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at offside.wire@gmail.com.
